Hardwired:






    Hardwired  



 Smoke CO OneLink Heat Smoke/CO MiscDiscontinued


BRK Smoke Alarms Models:7010B7020B9120AB9120B9120B-48B9120B-48P9120B6CPSA520B3120B7010BSL9120LBLSmoke AlarmsBRK® hardwired smoke alarms are designed to be easy to install, easy to maintain, and quality-engineered for years of virtually maintenance-free service. The full line includes models with special features like silence buttons, battery compartment locks, and extra-bright exit lights for specific applications. To the right are the features BRK® smoke alarms share.  Download Ion Smoke Alarms Certificate of Conformity ALL BRK Smoke Alarms»Meet UL 217 standard - single station smoke alarms.»Listed with California State Fire Marshal.»UL mandated repeating alarm horn pattern (85 dB)-3 beeps, pause, 3 beeps.»10-Year Limited WarrantyBRK CO Alarms Models:CO5120BNCO5120PDBNCO AlarmsBRK® hardwired carbon monoxide alarms are designed to be easy to install, easy to maintain, and quality-engineered for years of virtually maintenance-free service. The full line includes models with Contractor preferred features like silence buttons, battery compartment locks, "Quick-Connect" wiring harnesses and keyhole slots in the mounting bracket for easy installation. To the right are the features all BRK® carbon monoxide alarms share. ALL BRK CO Alarms»Meets UL 2034 standards - single and multiple station carbon monoxide alarms.»UL mandated repeating alarm horn pattern (85 dB)-4 fast beeps, pause, 4 fast beeps.»7-Year Limited WarrantyBRK OneLink Alarms Models:AC10-500BOneLink Alarms
Why should I offer Wi-Fi connected alarms?
Because homeowners are asking for them! They recently stated in a survey that 37% would like to control their smoke and CO alarms through their smart phones. From lighting control to garage door openers, they have a deep desire to be in control of their home environment and they are willing to pay for the convenience.
Let’s face it, homeowners interaction with smoke alarms has been either a nuisance or a frightful experience. Whether changing batteries due to that annoying low battery chirp in the middle of the night or trying to silence an alarm because they burned dinner, responding to or keeping tabs on the working condition of their alarms has always been a chore at best. Until Now!
First Alert Onelink Wi-Fi Alarms allow them to easily silence and monitor the alarm condition and events that take place inside their homes via an iPhone or iPad. They don’t even have to be home. Because the new Onelink Wi-Fi alarms have a sealed 10 year battery backup, they will never have to get on a ladder to change a battery again. With the free App and no special hub needed, connecting the alarms to a Wi-Fi network provides access to all installed alarms. They can even view multiple residences on one phone. The innovative features and design along with the intuitive interface on the app forever changes the experience of interacting with their smoke and CO alarms to a positive one.
Multi-Family   Rental Properties
Keeping tabs on the working condition of smoke and CO alarms in your tenants apartments or your rental properties has always been a chore. Trying to schedule time to inspect the alarms or change batteries can often be frustrating. In addition, if a smoke or CO event takes place you may not learn of it for weeks, if ever. Until now!
First Alert Onelink Wi-Fi Alarms allow you to easily monitor the alarm condition and events that take place inside your tenants residences via your iPhone or iPad without having to actually gain access to the property or even be in the building. With the free App and no special hub needed, just connect the alarms to a Wi-Fi network to have access to all installed alarms. Multiple residences can be viewed on one phone.
The ultimate upgrade in connectivity
Offering Onelink Wi-Fi alarms as an upgrade throughout the home provides the best option for the ultimate in connectivity. Your home buyer will appreciate you offer the latest state-of-the-art products. Whether luxury or standard build, First Alert Onelink Wi-Fi alarms satisfy this growing trend for a connected home.
Cost is a concern?
Need a more economical solution? Install only one hardwired Onelink Wi-Fi alarm. Then install and interconnect per building code standard BRK/First Alert hardwired alarms throughout the home. The standard alarms will provide notification a smoke or CO event occurred and will communicate - location unknown. In the future, Onelink Wi-Fi alarms can be swapped out as required. ALL BRK OneLink AlarmsWireless Interconnect
Bluetooth BLE communication between alarms and Wi-Fi to connect to your Apple smart phone or tablet.
Interconnects with all BRK/First Alert Hardwired Alarms
Reliable and secure Bluetooth BLE communication between alarms.
10YR CO Sensor/10YR Alarm Life/10YR Battery backup
10 year CO sensor and alarm life. Sealed, tamper proof batteries last 10 years.
Multi-Color Indicator Ring

Multi-color light ring provides visual indication of various alarm states. Green: Normal or completed operation; Blue: Voice prompts or Pairing; Red: Alarm/Warning; Amber: Malfunction/End of Life; White: Nightlight.
Voice Warning with Location
Programmable with up to 13 locations (ex. “basement”). When alarm sounds (if programmed for basement), it will say, “Warning, Evacuate, Smoke in Basement”.  If other Onelink Wi-Fi alarms are located throughout the house they will also signal, “Warning, Evacuate, Smoke in Basement”.
Flood Mesh Network Communication
2-way communication format that sends, receives and re-sends the alarm signals providing a more reliable network
Free App/Activity Log
App provides real time notification and history logging of all events by alarm so you can easily identify condition and troubleshoot incidents such as identifying initiating alarm or low battery condition.
Other Standard Features
Also includes Silence (Alarm and Low Battery), Photoelectric Smoke Sensor, Electrochemical CO Sensor, Spread Spectrum Horn Tone (easier heard by elderly), Smart Interconnect, Optipath 360 Technology, Intelligent Sensing Technology.BRK Heat Alarms Models:HD6135FBHeat AlarmsBRK® hardwired heat alarms are designed to be easy to install, easy to maintain, and quality-engineered for years of virtually maintenance-free service. The full line includes models with Contractor preferred features like silence buttons (HD6135FB only), battery compartment locks, "Quick-Connect" wiring harnesses and keyhole slots in the mounting bracket for easy installation. To the right are the features all BRK® heat alarms share. ALL BRK Heat Alarms»Meets UL 539 standard - single and multiple station heat alarm.»Listed with California State Fire Marshal.»UL mandated repeating alarm horn pattern (85 dB)-3 beeps, pause, 3 beeps.»10-Year Limited WarrantyBRK Smoke/CO Alarms Models:SC7010BSC7010BVSC9120BSC9120B6CPSC9120LBLSmoke/CO AlarmsBRK® hardwired combination smoke/carbon monoxide alarms are designed to be easy to install, easy to maintain, and quality-engineered for years of virtually maintenance-free service. The full line includes models with Contractor preferred features like silence buttons, battery compartment locks, "Quick-Connect" wiring harnesses and keyhole slots in the mounting bracket for easy installation. To the right are the features BRK® combination smoke/carbon monoxide alarms share. ALL BRK Smoke/CO Alarms»Meets both UL 217 & UL 2034 standards - single and multiple station smoke & carbon monoxide alarms.»UL mandated repeating alarm horn patterns (85 dB)-3 beeps, pause, 3 beeps and 4 fast beeps, pause, 4 fast beeps.»7-Year Limited WarrantyBRK Misc Models:RM4SL177-OLDSL177MiscBRK manufacturers other hardwired devices that meet the same high standards as with our smoke and carbon monoxode alarms.BRK Discontinued/Obsolete Models:
Smoke Alarms - Discontinued Models:100S7010912091206CP9120B-GFD9120LBSA773CN Smoke/CO Alarms - Discontinued Models:SC9120B-GFD Heat Alarms - Discontinued Models:HD6135FDiscontinued AlarmsDiscontinued BRK Items


 

