BRK, Inc.: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 26, 2017 2:22 PM ET
Building Products

Company Overview of BRK, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
BRK, Inc. develops and sells blind repair kits. Its blind repair kit product consists of a plastic mold, which provides seamless and invisible repairs for vertical blinds that have had their hanging hole ripped. The company was founded in 1998 and is based in Las Vegas, Nevada.


3871 South Valley View BoulevardUnit 70Las Vegas, NV 89103United StatesFounded in 1998



Phone: 702-572-8050

www.blindrepairkit.com







Key Executives for BRK, Inc.




Mr. Brian Keasberry


      	Treasurer & Secretary
      


Age: 55
        

Total Annual Compensation: $100.0K





Compensation as of Fiscal Year 2016. 

BRK, Inc. Key Developments

BRK, Inc. Announces Management Changes
Jul 17 17
BRK, Inc. announced that Daniel Serruya has been appointed to the Company's board of directors, which will now consist of solely of Mr. Serruya, and appointed as President and Chief Executive Officer of the Company. Simultaneously with Mr. Serruya's appointment, Gary Shields was appointed Chief Technology Officer, and Brian Keasberry resigned as a director, and President and Chief Executive Officer, but remains as the Company's Secretary and Treasurer. Mr. Serruaya has been a consultant, providing business development and structured financing advice and services. Mr. Shields has been a Technical Designer at Shark Marine Technologies, of St. Catharine's, Ontario, since August 2016. From February 2015 until July 2016, Mr. Shields was a Technical Designer at Niagara Technical Design, of Fonthill, Ontario.


BRK, Inc. announced delayed 10-Q filing
Mar 20 17
On 03/20/2017, BRK, Inc. announced that they will be unable to file their next 10-Q by the deadline required by the SEC.


Christopher Stramacchia Resigns to BRK, Inc. as Director and Chief Technology Officer
Mar 9 17
Effective February 28, 2017, Christopher Stramacchia, resigned as a director and Chief Technology Officer of BRK, Inc.


